## INMAIL GUIDANCE

Open Profiles only (free). Subject under 8 words.

**Subject line:**
```
Replace junior reps with AI agents?
```

**Body:**
```
Hey [First Name],

Most AI sales tools just book meetings. We built an actual sales agent.

Handles inbound and outbound calls, knows your product inside-out from day one (pricing, specs, integrations), and costs ~$3K/month vs $60K-$100K for a junior rep.

No ramp time. No training. Just execution capacity that compounds monthly.

My co-founders and I scaled and exited our own B2B services company — we built this because we needed it.

Can I send you a demo?

— Chris
```

---

## POST ENGAGEMENT GUIDANCE

**Posts to like:** Founder content, B2B sales challenges, AI in business, agency/services company growth, operator stories.

**Posts to comment on:** Posts about sales hiring struggles, SDR costs, AI adoption in business, founder-led sales fatigue.

**Comment voice:** Sharp, operator-to-operator. One sentence that adds real perspective. Never generic.

**Good comment examples:**
- "This is exactly where most founders get stuck — sales doesn't scale until it's off your plate."
- "The ramp time on a new sales rep is brutal. AI solving this is the obvious next step."

---

## SKIP RULES

1. Skip "Saved" leads — already contacted
2. Skip 1st-degree connections — already connected
3. Skip 3rd-degree connections — flag high-value ones as InMail candidates
4. Skip leads clearly outside the target ICP

